# vanDerPol.nim
## Compilation
```sh
nim c -r -d:fmu vanDerPol.nim
```

## Testing
```sh
../fmuCheck.linux64 -h 0.2 -s 5 -f -l 6 -e vanDerPol.log vanDerPol.fmu
```
This creates the log file: [vanDerPol.log](https://github.com/mantielero/fmu.nim/blob/main/examples/vanDerPol/vanDerPol.log).
